date - displays the current date and time

Description:
The date command prints the current date and time in a human-readable format. By default, it shows the local time. You can adjust the displayed time with the optional -zone=<offset> flag, where <offset> is the number of hours to add or subtract from local time (valid range: -12 to +14).

Usage:
date [-zone=<offset>]

Examples:
date # Output: Current date: Sat Sep 6 14:30:15 2025
date -zone=2 # Output: Current date: Sat Sep 6 16:30:15 2025
date -zone=-5 # Output: Current date: Sat Sep 6 09:30:15 2025
date -zone=20 # Error: Invalid time zone offset. Must be between -12 and 14.
